<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Pablo Iranzo Gómez's blog - LED kit</title><link>https://iranzo.io/</link><description>A bunch of unrelated data</description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 12 Oct 2020 20:32:34 +0200</lastBuildDate><item><title>Lego Porsche 911 Led Kit</title><link>https://iranzo.io/blog/2020/10/12/lego-porsche-911-led-kit/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;As with other kits, I bought the Led kit for the &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.es/dp/B01CCT2ZHC?tag=redken-21"&gt;Porsche 911 &lt;span class="caps"&gt;GT3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="caps"&gt;RS&lt;/span&gt; 🛒&lt;/a&gt; (more pics at &lt;a href="https://iranzo.io/blog/2020/02/21/lego-bugatti-chiron-and-porsche-911-gt3-rs/"&gt;Porsche 911 &lt;span class="caps"&gt;GT3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and just received my &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.es/dp/B07C31ZFDM?tag=redken-21"&gt;&lt;span class="caps"&gt;LED&lt;/span&gt; Kit 🛒&lt;/a&gt; (or &lt;a href="https://s.click.aliexpress.com/e/_eKUAhL"&gt;AliExpress 🛒&lt;/a&gt;) after my experience with the &lt;a href="https://iranzo.io/blog/2020/09/25/lego-bugatti-chiron-led-kit/"&gt;Bugatti Chiron&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Instructions were a photocopy which was hard to read, but seller provided electronic copy that was easier to&amp;nbsp;understand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The kit&amp;nbsp;contains:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="caps"&gt;LED&lt;/span&gt; for front lights (main&amp;nbsp;lights)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="caps"&gt;LED&lt;/span&gt; for rear lights&amp;nbsp;(brake)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="caps"&gt;LED&lt;/span&gt; for the ceiling (driver&amp;nbsp;area)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="caps"&gt;USB&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;connector&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start installing them from the rear part, it will be easier to drive the wires trough the vehicle, it just comes with some bagged cables + pieces for each area listed&amp;nbsp;above.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check the&amp;nbsp;results:&lt;/p&gt;
